I think you need to add `targetCompatibility` attribute with `sourceCompatibility` in gradle to target your `java` version.

        allprojects {
        apply plugin: &#39;java&#39;
        sourceCompatibility = 1.6
        targetCompatibility = 1.6
    }
Also need to check `java` default path in `gradle.properties` file with version your project is use.

You need to check [Can’t build Java 1.8 even with proper Java version in use](https://discuss.gradle.org/t/cant-build-java-1-8-even-with-proper-java-version-in-use/2461) and [Gradle finds wrong JAVA_HOME even though it&#39;s correctly set](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22307516/gradle-finds-wrong-java-home-even-though-its-correctly-set) to get more idea about set `java` compile version gradle.

